        "tradition": "OCF",
        "date": "ca. 800",
        "description": "Perhaps only slightly younger than Gellone. Contains the earliest text specifically associated with the inauguration of a king: 'quando elevatur in regno.' Two royal benedictions and a mass for the king. The Gelasian sacramentary, Gellone, Autun, and Angoulême variants are given together."
      }
